ore":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003e\"If I had looked at the lexical search and BM25 space in 2016, I would have said it was solved, and that catching up would be nearly impossible.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis interview with Tantivy creator Paul Masurel looks at how wrong I would have been; discussing challenging solved domains, open-source competition done right, and why long-fermented frustration is an underrated driver.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"\"If I had looked at the lexical search and BM25 space in 2016, I would have said it was solved, and that catching up would be nearly impossible.\"\r\n\r\nThis interview with Tantivy creator Paul Masurel looks at how wrong I would have been; discussing challenging solved domains, open-source competition done right, and why long-fermented frustration is an underrated driver.","submitter_user":"jamesgresql","user_is_author":true,"tags":["databases"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9eg0hs","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9eg0hs/conversation_with_paul_masurel_creator"}]